[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1285},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F01\u002Fthinkphp-day-30-deploy-to-heroku\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F01\u002Fthinkphp-day-30-deploy-to-heroku\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F01\u002Fthinkphp-day-30-deploy-to-heroku\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F01\u002Fthinkphp-day-30-deploy-to-heroku\u002F":1260,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F01\u002Fthinkphp-day-30-deploy-to-heroku\u002F":1269},"\u002Fphp\u002F20191001\u002F106986397\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1241,"date":1242,"description":1243,"extension":1244,"lang":1245,"meta":1246,"navigation":900,"path":1247,"readingMinutes":1248,"seo":1249,"standalone":1250,"stem":1251,"tags":1252,"tldr":1257,"updated":1242,"url":1258,"__hash__":1259},"content\u002Fen\u002FPHP\u002Fthinkphp-day-30-deploy-to-heroku.md","Day 30 - Learning ThinkPHP from Scratch: Deploying to Heroku","1002819167",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1227},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,36,40,43,73,80,87,94,99,110,116,127,137,140,159,166,172,176,185,191,197,203,210,216,219,230,237,241,244,291,298,398,416,756,762,768,775,781,785,788,793,804,808,826,836,840,843,849,856,867,873,877,891,1170,1174,1177,1180,1186,1193,1200,1207,1215,1223],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Time to actually ship the thing. In this post I'll walk you through deploying the ThinkPHP system we've been building over the last few chapters onto Heroku.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"heroku","Heroku",[17,25,26],{},"Heroku is a service a lot of people love, and honestly I'm one of them. I won't spend too long introducing it here though — plenty of people have already covered it better than I could, so I'll just point you at a write-up from someone who's been down this road before:",[17,28,29],{},[30,31,35],"a",{"href":32,"rel":33},"https:\u002F\u002Fithelp.ithome.com.tw\u002Farticles\u002F10196129",[34],"nofollow","Publishing a site to Heroku (article in Mandarin)",[12,37,39],{"id":38},"deploying-thinkphp-to-heroku","Deploying ThinkPHP to Heroku",[17,41,42],{},"First, move into your project directory and run these one by one:",[44,45,50],"pre",{"className":46,"code":47,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-git shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","git init\ngit add .\ngit commit -m 'first'\n","git","",[51,52,53,61,67],"code",{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,55,58],"span",{"class":56,"line":57},"line",1,[54,59,60],{},"git init\n",[54,62,64],{"class":56,"line":63},2,[54,65,66],{},"git add .\n",[54,68,70],{"class":56,"line":69},3,[54,71,72],{},"git commit -m 'first'\n",[17,74,75,76,79],{},"Next we need to create a Heroku app. The command for that is ",[51,77,78],{},"heroku create"," (heads up — run this inside your project directory):",[17,81,82],{},[83,84],"img",{"alt":85,"src":86},"Creating the app","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FUZ9k3Cr.png",[17,88,89,90,93],{},"Once that's done, you'll see the freshly created app — mine's called ",[51,91,92],{},"obscure-mountain-83772"," — show up in your Heroku dashboard:",[17,95,96],{},[83,97],{"alt":92,"src":98},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fivm7sfm.png",[17,100,101,102,105,106,109],{},"Now you just run ",[51,103,104],{},"git push heroku master"," and it'll deploy. But if you visit the URL right after, you'll probably hit a ",[51,107,108],{},"403 Forbidden",":",[17,111,112],{},[83,113],{"alt":114,"src":115},"403","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FItVtgWy.png",[17,117,118,119,122,123,126],{},"The reason is that we never told Heroku to use the ",[51,120,121],{},"public"," folder as the document root. So in your project's root directory, create a file called ",[51,124,125],{},"Procfile"," with this content:",[44,128,131],{"className":129,"code":130,"language":125,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-Procfile shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","web: vendor\u002Fbin\u002Fheroku-php-apache2 public\n",[51,132,133],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,134,135],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,136,130],{},[17,138,139],{},"Then run these:",[44,141,143],{"className":46,"code":142,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"git add .\ngit commit -m \"add to procfile\"\ngit push heroku master\n",[51,144,145,149,154],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,146,147],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,148,66],{},[54,150,151],{"class":56,"line":63},[54,152,153],{},"git commit -m \"add to procfile\"\n",[54,155,156],{"class":56,"line":69},[54,157,158],{},"git push heroku master\n",[17,160,161,162,165],{},"Now if you visit ",[51,163,164],{},"https:\u002F\u002Fobscure-mountain-83772.herokuapp.com\u002F",", you should see ThinkPHP up and running:",[17,167,168],{},[83,169],{"alt":170,"src":171},"ThinkPHP","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fztxt2vq.png",[12,173,175],{"id":174},"setting-up-the-database","Setting up the database",[17,177,178,179,184],{},"If you head over to the ",[30,180,183],{"href":181,"rel":182},"https:\u002F\u002Fobscure-mountain-83772.herokuapp.com\u002Fmessage\u002F",[34],"message board page"," at this point, you'll run into an error:",[17,186,187],{},[83,188],{"alt":189,"src":190},"Error message","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fg2Dpgwx.png",[17,192,193,194,109],{},"That's because we haven't created a database yet. So let's fix that. Start by running Heroku's command to add a database — ",[51,195,196],{},"heroku addons:add cleardb",[17,198,199],{},[83,200],{"alt":201,"src":202},"Creating the database","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FxXQAOxZ.png",[17,204,205,206,209],{},"Then run ",[51,207,208],{},"heroku config"," to see the database connection details:",[17,211,212],{},[83,213],{"alt":214,"src":215},"config","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVGzbjNj.png",[17,217,218],{},"That long string breaks down like this:",[44,220,224],{"className":221,"code":222,"language":223,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-mysql shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","mysql:\u002F\u002F[username]:[password]@[host]\u002F[database name]?reconnect=true\n","mysql",[51,225,226],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,227,228],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,229,222],{},[17,231,232,233,236],{},"So take those values and fill them into your project's ",[51,234,235],{},"config\u002Fdatabase.php",", then push again. That's it for the database connection.",[12,238,240],{"id":239},"migrating-the-database","Migrating the database",[17,242,243],{},"Next we need to get our tables and default data into the database. This is where the migrations and seeds we covered in the previous chapter come in. Just run these one at a time in your terminal:",[44,245,249],{"className":246,"code":247,"language":248,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-php shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","heroku run php think migrate:run\nheroku run php think seed:run\n","php",[51,250,251,274],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,252,253,256,259,262,265,268,271],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,254,22],{"class":255},"sCcAr",[54,257,258],{"class":255}," run",[54,260,261],{"class":255}," php",[54,263,264],{"class":255}," think",[54,266,267],{"class":255}," migrate",[54,269,109],{"class":270},"sMAXC",[54,272,273],{"class":255},"run\n",[54,275,276,278,280,282,284,287,289],{"class":56,"line":63},[54,277,22],{"class":255},[54,279,258],{"class":255},[54,281,261],{"class":255},[54,283,264],{"class":255},[54,285,286],{"class":255}," seed",[54,288,109],{"class":270},[54,290,273],{"class":255},[17,292,293,294,297],{},"But when you run ",[51,295,296],{},"heroku run php think migrate:run",", you'll probably hit this error:",[44,299,301],{"className":246,"code":300,"language":248,"meta":49,"style":49},"  [PDOException]\n  SQLSTATE[HY000]: General error: 1293 Incorrect table definition; there can be only one TIMESTAMP column with CURRENT_TIMESTAMP in DEFAULT or ON UPDATE clause\n",[51,302,303,314],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,304,305,308,311],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,306,307],{"class":270},"  [",[54,309,310],{"class":255},"PDOException",[54,312,313],{"class":270},"]\n",[54,315,316,319,322,325,328,331,334,337,340,343,346,349,352,355,358,361,364,367,370,373,376,379,382,385,389,392,395],{"class":56,"line":63},[54,317,318],{"class":255},"  SQLSTATE",[54,320,321],{"class":270},"[",[54,323,324],{"class":255},"HY000",[54,326,327],{"class":270},"]: ",[54,329,330],{"class":255},"General",[54,332,333],{"class":255}," error",[54,335,336],{"class":270},": ",[54,338,339],{"class":255},"1293",[54,341,342],{"class":255}," Incorrect",[54,344,345],{"class":255}," table",[54,347,348],{"class":255}," definition",[54,350,351],{"class":270},"; ",[54,353,354],{"class":255},"there",[54,356,357],{"class":255}," can",[54,359,360],{"class":255}," be",[54,362,363],{"class":255}," only",[54,365,366],{"class":255}," one",[54,368,369],{"class":255}," TIMESTAMP",[54,371,372],{"class":255}," column",[54,374,375],{"class":255}," with",[54,377,378],{"class":255}," CURRENT_TIMESTAMP",[54,380,381],{"class":255}," in",[54,383,384],{"class":255}," DEFAULT",[54,386,388],{"class":387},"sWyjQ"," or",[54,390,391],{"class":255}," ON",[54,393,394],{"class":255}," UPDATE",[54,396,397],{"class":255}," clause\n",[17,399,400,401,404,405,408,409,412,413,415],{},"The cause is that the database only allows a single column with ",[51,402,403],{},"CURRENT_TIMESTAMP",". So we need to tweak our ",[51,406,407],{},"think_message"," migration. By default, phinx's ",[51,410,411],{},"timestamp"," type uses ",[51,414,403],{},", so we change it to this:",[44,417,419],{"className":246,"code":418,"language":248,"meta":49,"style":49},"public function up()\n{\n    $table = $this->table('message');\n    $table->addColumn('title', 'string', ['limit'=> 15, 'default'=>'', 'comment' => 'Title'])\n    ->addColumn('content', 'text', ['default'=>'', 'comment' => 'Message content'])\n    ->addColumn('author', 'string', ['limit'=> 20, 'default'=>'', 'comment' => 'Author'])\n    ->addColumn('email', 'string', ['limit'=> 128, 'default'=>'', 'comment' => 'Email'])\n    ->addColumn('create_time', 'timestamp', ['default'=>'0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'comment' => 'Created time']) \u002F\u002F the key change: set this default to 0000-00-00 00:00:00\n    ->addColumn('last_modify_time', 'timestamp', ['default'=>'CURRENT_TIMESTAMP','update' => 'CURRENT_TIMESTAMP', 'comment' => 'Updated time'])\n    ->create();\n}\n",[51,420,421,435,440,467,525,562,606,650,692,739,750],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,422,423,425,428,432],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,424,121],{"class":387},[54,426,427],{"class":387}," function",[54,429,431],{"class":430},"sj_SG"," up",[54,433,434],{"class":270},"()\n",[54,436,437],{"class":56,"line":63},[54,438,439],{"class":270},"{\n",[54,441,442,445,448,451,454,457,460,464],{"class":56,"line":69},[54,443,444],{"class":270},"    $table ",[54,446,447],{"class":387},"=",[54,449,450],{"class":255}," $this",[54,452,453],{"class":387},"->",[54,455,456],{"class":430},"table",[54,458,459],{"class":270},"(",[54,461,463],{"class":462},"sTRMh","'message'",[54,465,466],{"class":270},");\n",[54,468,470,473,475,478,480,483,486,489,492,495,498,501,503,506,508,511,513,516,519,522],{"class":56,"line":469},4,[54,471,472],{"class":270},"    $table",[54,474,453],{"class":387},[54,476,477],{"class":430},"addColumn",[54,479,459],{"class":270},[54,481,482],{"class":462},"'title'",[54,484,485],{"class":270},", ",[54,487,488],{"class":462},"'string'",[54,490,491],{"class":270},", [",[54,493,494],{"class":462},"'limit'",[54,496,497],{"class":387},"=>",[54,499,500],{"class":255}," 15",[54,502,485],{"class":270},[54,504,505],{"class":462},"'default'",[54,507,497],{"class":387},[54,509,510],{"class":462},"''",[54,512,485],{"class":270},[54,514,515],{"class":462},"'comment'",[54,517,518],{"class":387}," =>",[54,520,521],{"class":462}," 'Title'",[54,523,524],{"class":270},"])\n",[54,526,528,531,533,535,538,540,543,545,547,549,551,553,555,557,560],{"class":56,"line":527},5,[54,529,530],{"class":387},"    ->",[54,532,477],{"class":430},[54,534,459],{"class":270},[54,536,537],{"class":462},"'content'",[54,539,485],{"class":270},[54,541,542],{"class":462},"'text'",[54,544,491],{"class":270},[54,546,505],{"class":462},[54,548,497],{"class":387},[54,550,510],{"class":462},[54,552,485],{"class":270},[54,554,515],{"class":462},[54,556,518],{"class":387},[54,558,559],{"class":462}," 'Message content'",[54,561,524],{"class":270},[54,563,565,567,569,571,574,576,578,580,582,584,587,589,591,593,595,597,599,601,604],{"class":56,"line":564},6,[54,566,530],{"class":387},[54,568,477],{"class":430},[54,570,459],{"class":270},[54,572,573],{"class":462},"'author'",[54,575,485],{"class":270},[54,577,488],{"class":462},[54,579,491],{"class":270},[54,581,494],{"class":462},[54,583,497],{"class":387},[54,585,586],{"class":255}," 20",[54,588,485],{"class":270},[54,590,505],{"class":462},[54,592,497],{"class":387},[54,594,510],{"class":462},[54,596,485],{"class":270},[54,598,515],{"class":462},[54,600,518],{"class":387},[54,602,603],{"class":462}," 'Author'",[54,605,524],{"class":270},[54,607,609,611,613,615,618,620,622,624,626,628,631,633,635,637,639,641,643,645,648],{"class":56,"line":608},7,[54,610,530],{"class":387},[54,612,477],{"class":430},[54,614,459],{"class":270},[54,616,617],{"class":462},"'email'",[54,619,485],{"class":270},[54,621,488],{"class":462},[54,623,491],{"class":270},[54,625,494],{"class":462},[54,627,497],{"class":387},[54,629,630],{"class":255}," 128",[54,632,485],{"class":270},[54,634,505],{"class":462},[54,636,497],{"class":387},[54,638,510],{"class":462},[54,640,485],{"class":270},[54,642,515],{"class":462},[54,644,518],{"class":387},[54,646,647],{"class":462}," 'Email'",[54,649,524],{"class":270},[54,651,653,655,657,659,662,664,667,669,671,673,676,678,680,682,685,688],{"class":56,"line":652},8,[54,654,530],{"class":387},[54,656,477],{"class":430},[54,658,459],{"class":270},[54,660,661],{"class":462},"'create_time'",[54,663,485],{"class":270},[54,665,666],{"class":462},"'timestamp'",[54,668,491],{"class":270},[54,670,505],{"class":462},[54,672,497],{"class":387},[54,674,675],{"class":462},"'0000-00-00 00:00:00'",[54,677,485],{"class":270},[54,679,515],{"class":462},[54,681,518],{"class":387},[54,683,684],{"class":462}," 'Created time'",[54,686,687],{"class":270},"]) ",[54,689,691],{"class":690},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F the key change: set this default to 0000-00-00 00:00:00\n",[54,693,695,697,699,701,704,706,708,710,712,714,717,720,723,725,728,730,732,734,737],{"class":56,"line":694},9,[54,696,530],{"class":387},[54,698,477],{"class":430},[54,700,459],{"class":270},[54,702,703],{"class":462},"'last_modify_time'",[54,705,485],{"class":270},[54,707,666],{"class":462},[54,709,491],{"class":270},[54,711,505],{"class":462},[54,713,497],{"class":387},[54,715,716],{"class":462},"'CURRENT_TIMESTAMP'",[54,718,719],{"class":270},",",[54,721,722],{"class":462},"'update'",[54,724,518],{"class":387},[54,726,727],{"class":462}," 'CURRENT_TIMESTAMP'",[54,729,485],{"class":270},[54,731,515],{"class":462},[54,733,518],{"class":387},[54,735,736],{"class":462}," 'Updated time'",[54,738,524],{"class":270},[54,740,742,744,747],{"class":56,"line":741},10,[54,743,530],{"class":387},[54,745,746],{"class":430},"create",[54,748,749],{"class":270},"();\n",[54,751,753],{"class":56,"line":752},11,[54,754,755],{"class":270},"}\n",[17,757,758,759,761],{},"Push again, run ",[51,760,296],{}," one more time, and the problem's gone:",[17,763,764],{},[83,765],{"alt":766,"src":767},"Problem solved","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLkyUg7I.png",[17,769,770,771,774],{},"Seeding the data works the same way — just run ",[51,772,773],{},"heroku run php think seed:run"," and your data gets filled in:",[17,776,777],{},[83,778],{"alt":779,"src":780},"Seeding data","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FsVsi4Km.png",[12,782,784],{"id":783},"deployment-gotchas","Deployment gotchas",[17,786,787],{},"You'll probably run into a few snags along the way, so here are the fixes.",[789,790,792],"h3",{"id":791},"css-js-files-disappear","CSS \u002F JS files disappear",[17,794,795,796,799,800,803],{},"The main culprit is a ",[51,797,798],{},".gitignore"," sitting inside ",[51,801,802],{},"public\u002Fstatic",". Delete it, redeploy to Heroku, and you're good.",[789,805,807],{"id":806},"after-seeding-call-to-undefined-function-mb_substr","After seeding: Call to undefined function mb_substr()",[17,809,810,811,814,815,818,819,822,823,825],{},"Open ",[51,812,813],{},"composer.json"," and add ",[51,816,817],{},"\"mbstring\": \"*\""," under ",[51,820,821],{},"require",", then redeploy. The reason is that the Heroku environment doesn't have this extension, so we use ",[51,824,813],{}," to tell Heroku we need it.",[17,827,828,829,831,832,835],{},"After adding ",[51,830,817],{},", remember to run ",[51,833,834],{},"composer update"," — otherwise pushing to Heroku won't actually change anything.",[789,837,839],{"id":838},"the-captcha-vanishes","The captcha vanishes",[17,841,842],{},"You'll notice the captcha just refuses to show up:",[17,844,845],{},[83,846],{"alt":847,"src":848},"Captcha missing","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fc7K71c6.png",[17,850,851,852,855],{},"And if you visit the captcha route directly, you'll get this error: ",[51,853,854],{},"Call to undefined function think\\captcha\\imagecreate()",".",[17,857,858,859,818,862,864,865,109],{},"The fix is to add ",[51,860,861],{},"\"ext-gd\": \"*\"",[51,863,821],{}," in ",[51,866,813],{},[17,868,869],{},[83,870],{"alt":871,"src":872},"Captcha showing correctly","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FRwoJQ8k.png",[789,874,876],{"id":875},"new-posts-have-no-created-time","New posts have no created time",[17,878,879,880,883,884,886,887,890],{},"Because of the ",[51,881,882],{},"only one TIMESTAMP column with CURRENT_TIMESTAMP in DEFAULT or ON UPDATE clause"," situation, we can't rely on ",[51,885,403],{}," to auto-fill the created time. So I made a small tweak to the method that saves a post — ",[51,888,889],{},"save()",". Just change it to this:",[44,892,894],{"className":246,"code"